=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Private Agencies Contracted for E-Vape Enforcement Activities
Date: 2025-10-14
Source: Singapore Parliament
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Oral Answer)
Topic: Vaping, Enforcement, Health Sciences Authority (HSA), Subcontractors

Summary:
- Question about the number of private enforcement agencies subcontracted by HSA, total staff in these agencies, and whether Police will take over enforcement given the harsher stance on e-vaporisers.
- Ministry of Health / HSA response: Enforcement is whole-of-Government. Over 10,000 officers from various agencies, including Singapore Police Force, are involved. HSA additionally contracts ~100 staff from an external enforcement vendor to reinforce its enforcement team.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
- Singapore Police Force (SPF)
- Private enforcement vendor (~100 staff)
- Mr Fadli Fawzi, MP (Aljunied GRC)

Key Concepts:
- Whole-of-Government enforcement effort
- HSA subcontracting private staff for e-vaporiser enforcement
- Enforcement scale: 10,000+ officers across agencies
- Consideration of Police-led enforcement

Body:
1. Enforcement against e-vaporiser offences is coordinated across multiple government agencies.
2. HSA engages about 100 staff from external vendors to supplement its enforcement team.
3. Total enforcement force: over 10,000 officers including SPF.
4. No indication that Police will replace HSA; enforcement remains multi-agency.

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH), Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
Date of Issue: 2025-10-14
